---
import Layout from '../../../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import PageShell from '../../../../components/PageShell.astro';
import CTABox from '../../../../components/CTABox.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const title = "Japan Work Visa Insurance Guide 2026 | Engineer/Specialist & HSP Requirements";
const description = "Complete guide to Japan work visa insurance requirements. Covers Engineer/Specialist visa, Highly Skilled Professional points system, Shakai Hoken enrollment, and health coverage for working in Japan.";

const tocItems = [
  { id: "overview", label: "Overview" },
  { id: "quick-decision", label: "Is This Right for You?" },
  { id: "official-requirements", label: "Official Requirements" },
  { id: "insurance-requirements", label: "Insurance Requirements" },
  { id: "recommended-providers", label: "Recommended Providers" },
  { id: "costs", label: "Costs Breakdown" },
  { id: "application-timeline", label: "Application Timeline" },
  { id: "scenarios", label: "Real-World Scenarios" },
  { id: "common-mistakes", label: "Common Mistakes" },
  { id: "healthcare-access", label: "Healthcare Access" },
  { id: "faq", label: "FAQs" },
  { id: "verdict", label: "Final Verdict" }
];
---

<Layout title={title} description={description}>
  <PageShell
    title="Japan Work Visa Insurance Guide"
    subtitle="Your complete guide to working legally in Japan with proper health coverage"
    heroImage="/images/countries/japan-hero-bg.png"
    tocItems={tocItems}
  >
    <!-- Quick Facts Box -->
    <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 mb-8">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-primary-900 mb-4">Quick Facts: Japan Work Visa</h3>
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-4 text-sm">
        <div><strong>Main Visa Type:</strong> Engineer/Specialist in Humanities (技人国)</div>
        <div><strong>Initial Duration:</strong> 1, 3, or 5 years</div>
        <div><strong>Salary Requirement:</strong> ~¥3M/year minimum (role dependent)</div>
        <div><strong>Processing Time:</strong> 1-3 months</div>
        <div><strong>Health Insurance:</strong> Shakai Hoken (mandatory employer coverage)</div>
        <div><strong>PR Pathway:</strong> 10 years (or 1-3 years with HSP visa)</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Overview -->
    <section id="overview" class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Overview</h2>

      <p class="text-neutral-700 mb-4">
        Japan's work visa system is based on "status of residence" categories, each tied to specific job types. The most common for skilled foreign workers is the Engineer/Specialist in Humanities/International Services (技術・人文知識・国際業務) visa, which covers IT, engineering, business, translation, marketing, and similar professional roles.
      </p>

      <p class="text-neutral-700 mb-4">
        The Highly Skilled Professional (HSP) visa, introduced in 2012 and enhanced since, offers a points-based fast track for talented professionals. Scoring 70+ points (based on education, salary, age, and achievements) grants a 5-year visa with spouse work rights and a path to permanent residence in just 3 years (or 1 year with 80+ points).
      </p>

      <p class="text-neutral-700 mb-4">
        Japan's health insurance is employer-provided through Shakai Hoken (社会保険), covering medical, pension, and unemployment insurance. Employees and employers split contributions roughly 50/50. The system provides excellent coverage at 70% reimbursement, with most workers adding private insurance for the 30% copay and enhanced benefits.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- Quick Decision Guide -->
    <section id="quick-decision" class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Is a Japan Work Visa Right for You?</h2>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
        <div class="bg-green-50 border border-green-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-green-900 mb-3">Good Fit If You...</h3>
          <ul class="space-y-2 text-green-800">
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-green-600 mt-1">✓</span>
              <span>Have a job offer from a Japanese company</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-green-600 mt-1">✓</span>
              <span>Work in IT, engineering, or skilled services</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-green-600 mt-1">✓</span>
              <span>Are excited by Japanese culture and lifestyle</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-green-600 mt-1">✓</span>
              <span>Want access to excellent, affordable healthcare</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-green-600 mt-1">✓</span>
              <span>Have university degree in relevant field</span>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-amber-900 mb-3">Consider Alternatives If...</h3>
          <ul class="space-y-2 text-amber-800">
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-amber-600 mt-1">→</span>
              <span>You don't speak or won't learn Japanese</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-amber-600 mt-1">→</span>
              <span>You want highest possible salary (Japan salaries are moderate)</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-amber-600 mt-1">→</span>
              <span>Work-life balance is your top priority</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-amber-600 mt-1">→</span>
              <span>You lack degree in field matching job offer</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-amber-600 mt-1">→</span>
              <span>You prefer remote/flexible work arrangements</span>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Official Requirements -->
    <section id="official-requirements" class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Official Requirements</h2>

      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-800 mb-3">Status of Residence Categories</h3>

      <ComparisonTable
        columns={["Visa Category", "Duration", "Requirements", "Best For"]}
        rows={[
          ["Engineer/Specialist in Humanities", "1, 3, or 5 years", "Degree + relevant job offer", "IT, engineering, business, marketing"],
          ["Highly Skilled Professional (HSP-1b)", "5 years", "70+ points", "Fast-track professionals"],
          ["Intra-Company Transferee", "1, 3, or 5 years", "1+ year with company", "Internal transfers"],
          ["Business Manager", "1, 3, or 5 years", "¥5M capital + office", "Entrepreneurs, executives"],
          ["Skilled Labor", "1, 3, or 5 years", "10+ years experience", "Chefs, craftspeople, specialists"]
        ]}
      />

      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-800 mt-6 mb-3">Highly Skilled Professional Points System</h3>

      <ComparisonTable
        columns={["Category", "Criteria", "Points Available"]}
        rows={[
          ["Education", "Doctorate, Master's, Bachelor's, multiple degrees", "5-30 points"],
          ["Work Experience", "Years of relevant experience", "5-25 points"],
          ["Annual Salary", "¥3M to ¥10M+ ranges", "0-40 points"],
          ["Age", "Under 30 to under 40", "5-15 points"],
          ["Achievements", "Patents, publications, awards, Japanese language", "5-25 points bonus"],
          ["Bonus Points", "Top university, JLPT N1, growth industry, etc.", "10-20 points each"]
        ]}
      />

      <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-4 mt-4">
        <p class="text-blue-800 font-medium">HSP Benefits at 70+ Points</p>
        <p class="text-blue-700 text-sm mt-1">5-year visa, spouse can work, bring parents (with conditions), bring domestic helper. Permanent residence eligible after 3 years (or 1 year with 80+ points). Calculate your score at the Immigration Services Agency website.</p>
      </div>

      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-800 mt-6 mb-3">Required Documents</h3>

      <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-700">
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="text-primary-600 mt-1">•</span>
            <span><strong>Valid passport</strong> – At least 6 months validity</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="text-primary-600 mt-1">•</span>
            <span><strong>Certificate of Eligibility (COE)</strong> – Employer applies to Immigration Bureau</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="text-primary-600 mt-1">•</span>
            <span><strong>University degree certificate</strong> – Original or certified copy</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="text-primary-600 mt-1">•</span>
            <span><strong>Employment contract</strong> – Showing job duties, salary, duration</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="text-primary-600 mt-1">•</span>
            <span><strong>Company documents</strong> – Registration, financial statements</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="text-primary-600 mt-1">•</span>
            <span><strong>Photo</strong> – 4cm × 3cm, recent</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="text-primary-600 mt-1">•</span>
            <span><strong>Resume/CV</strong> – Showing education and work history</span>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-4 mt-4">
        <p class="text-amber-800 font-medium">Degree-Job Match Requirement</p>
        <p class="text-amber-700 text-sm mt-1">Your university degree must relate to the job you're taking. A computer science degree for an IT role is fine. A literature degree for an IT role may be rejected unless you have 10+ years relevant experience. This is strictly enforced.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Insurance Requirements -->
    <section id="insurance-requirements" class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Insurance Requirements</h2>

      <div class="bg-green-50 border border-green-200 rounded-lg p-4 mb-6">
        <p class="text-green-800 font-medium">✓ Shakai Hoken Enrollment is Automatic</p>
        <p class="text-green-700 text-sm mt-1">As an employee, your company enrolls you in Shakai Hoken (社会保険) from day one. This covers health insurance (Kenko Hoken), pension (Kosei Nenkin), and employment insurance. Contributions are split ~50/50 between you and employer.</p>
      </div>

      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-800 mb-3">How Japanese Health Insurance Works</h3>

      <ComparisonTable
        columns={["Component", "What It Covers", "Your Share"]}
        rows={[
          ["Kenko Hoken (Health)", "Medical care, hospital, prescriptions", "30% copay at point of care"],
          ["Kosei Nenkin (Pension)", "Retirement pension", "~9.15% of salary"],
          ["Koyou Hoken (Employment)", "Unemployment benefits", "~0.6% of salary"],
          ["Rousai Hoken (Workers Comp)", "Work-related injuries", "Employer pays 100%"]
        ]}
      />

      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-800 mt-6 mb-3">The 30% Copay System</h3>

      <p class="text-neutral-700 mb-4">
        Japanese health insurance covers 70% of medical costs, with patients paying 30% out of pocket at the time of service. This applies to doctor visits, hospital stays, prescriptions, and most care. The system is extremely affordable—a typical GP visit costs ¥1,000-2,000 (~$7-14) after insurance.
      </p>

      <ComparisonTable
        columns={["Service", "Full Cost", "Your 30% Share"]}
        rows={[
          ["GP consultation", "¥3,000-5,000", "¥900-1,500 (~$6-10)"],
          ["Specialist visit", "¥5,000-10,000", "¥1,500-3,000 (~$10-20)"],
          ["Prescription (common)", "¥1,000-3,000", "¥300-900 (~$2-6)"],
          ["Hospital stay (per day)", "¥10,000-30,000", "¥3,000-9,000 (~$20-60)"],
          ["MRI scan", "¥15,000-25,000", "¥4,500-7,500 (~$30-50)"]
        ]}
      />

      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-800 mt-6 mb-3">High-Cost Medical Expense Benefit</h3>

      <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-4">
        <p class="text-blue-800 font-medium">Kogaku Ryoyo-hi (高額療養費) - Monthly Cap</p>
        <p class="text-blue-700 text-sm mt-1">If your monthly medical expenses exceed a threshold (around ¥80,000-90,000 for most incomes), you're reimbursed the excess. This means even major surgery or cancer treatment has capped monthly costs. Apply for a Gengaku Nintei (限度額適用認定証) card in advance to avoid paying upfront.</p>
      </div>

      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-800 mt-6 mb-3">What's Not Covered</h3>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-4">
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Covered (30% copay)</h4>
          <ul class="text-neutral-600 text-sm space-y-1">
            <li>• All medically necessary care</li>
            <li>• Hospital stays (standard room)</li>
            <li>• Prescriptions</li>
            <li>• Surgery</li>
            <li>• Mental healthcare</li>
            <li>• Maternity (partial)</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-4">
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Not Covered</h4>
          <ul class="text-neutral-600 text-sm space-y-1">
            <li>• Private hospital rooms</li>
            <li>• Cosmetic procedures</li>
            <li>• Normal childbirth (lump sum instead)</li>
            <li>• Most dental (basic checkups only)</li>
            <li>• Glasses/contacts</li>
            <li>• Alternative medicine</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Recommended Providers -->
    <section id="recommended-providers" class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Recommended Insurance Providers</h2>

      <p class="text-neutral-700 mb-6">
        Shakai Hoken provides excellent core coverage. Many expats add private insurance for the 30% copay, enhanced hospital options, and non-covered services. Japanese domestic insurers and international providers both serve this market.
      </p>

      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-800 mb-3">Japanese Domestic Insurers (Top-up Coverage)</h3>

      <ComparisonTable
        columns={["Insurer", "Plan Type", "Monthly Cost", "Key Features"]}
        rows={[
          ["Aflac Japan", "Iryo Hoken (medical)", "¥3,000-8,000", "Largest foreign insurer in Japan, English support"],
          ["Sony Life", "Comprehensive", "¥5,000-15,000", "Good for families, wide coverage"],
          ["Nippon Life", "Iryo + Cancer", "¥4,000-10,000", "Strong cancer coverage"],
          ["MetLife Japan", "Medical supplement", "¥3,000-7,000", "International backing, English options"]
        ]}
      />

      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-800 mt-6 mb-3">International Providers</h3>

      <ComparisonTable
        columns={["Provider", "Best For", "Monthly Cost", "Key Features"]}
        rows={[
          ["Cigna Global", "Executives, families", "$200-450", "Global coverage, direct billing"],
          ["BUPA Global", "Mental health priority", "$180-400", "No therapy limits"],
          ["Allianz Care", "European expats", "$150-350", "Strong Japan network"],
          ["Now Health", "Value seekers", "$120-280", "Asia-Pacific focus"],
          ["SafetyWing", "Short-term/nomads", "$50-100", "Basic supplemental coverage"]
        ]}
      />

      <CTABox
        title="Compare Supplemental Insurance for Japan"
        description="Find coverage for the 30% copay and enhanced benefits on top of Shakai Hoken."
        buttonText="Compare Plans"
        buttonHref="/best/expat-health-insurance"
      />
    </section>

    <!-- Costs Breakdown -->
    <section id="costs" class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Costs Breakdown</h2>

      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-800 mb-3">Visa & Setup Costs</h3>

      <ComparisonTable
        columns={["Item", "Cost (JPY)", "Cost (USD)", "Notes"]}
        rows={[
          ["Certificate of Eligibility", "¥0", "$0", "Free (employer applies)"],
          ["Visa stamp at embassy", "¥0-¥8,000", "$0-55", "Depends on nationality"],
          ["Residence card (Zairyu)", "¥0", "$0", "Issued at airport on arrival"],
          ["City registration", "¥0", "$0", "Required within 14 days"],
          ["My Number card", "¥0", "$0", "Free, takes 1-2 months"]
        ]}
      />

      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-800 mt-6 mb-3">Shakai Hoken Contributions</h3>

      <ComparisonTable
        columns={["Insurance Type", "Employee Share", "Employer Share", "Notes"]}
        rows={[
          ["Kenko Hoken (Health)", "~5% of salary", "~5% of salary", "Varies by prefecture"],
          ["Kosei Nenkin (Pension)", "~9.15% of salary", "~9.15% of salary", "Fixed nationwide"],
          ["Koyou Hoken (Employment)", "~0.6% of salary", "~0.95% of salary", "Unemployment benefits"],
          ["Total", "~15% of salary", "~15% of salary", "Split roughly 50/50"]
        ]}
      />

      <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
        <p class="text-blue-800 font-medium">Pension Refund (Lump-sum Withdrawal)</p>
        <p class="text-blue-700 text-sm mt-1">If you leave Japan permanently after 6+ months of contributions, you can claim back a portion of pension contributions (up to 5 years worth). Apply within 2 years of departure. Not full refund, but significant—often ¥500,000-2,000,000 depending on salary and tenure.</p>
      </div>

      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-800 mt-6 mb-3">Living Costs (Monthly)</h3>

      <ComparisonTable
        columns={["Category", "Tokyo", "Other Cities", "Notes"]}
        rows={[
          ["Rent (1BR/1K)", "¥80,000-150,000", "¥50,000-80,000", "Tokyo is expensive"],
          ["Utilities", "¥10,000-20,000", "¥8,000-15,000", "Gas, electric, water"],
          ["Transport", "¥10,000-20,000", "¥5,000-15,000", "Train pass if employer doesn't cover"],
          ["Food", "¥40,000-80,000", "¥30,000-60,000", "Eating out is affordable"],
          ["Healthcare (OOP)", "¥2,000-10,000", "¥2,000-10,000", "30% copays"]
        ]}
      />
    </section>

    <!-- Application Timeline -->
    <section id="application-timeline" class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Application Timeline</h2>

      <div class="space-y-4">
        <div class="flex gap-4">
          <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-24 text-sm font-medium text-primary-600">Month 1</div>
          <div class="flex-grow border-l-2 border-primary-200 pl-4 pb-4">
            <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Job Offer & Documentation</h4>
            <p class="text-neutral-600 text-sm">Accept job offer. Gather documents (degree certificates, resume, passport copy). Employer prepares Certificate of Eligibility (COE) application.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="flex gap-4">
          <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-24 text-sm font-medium text-primary-600">Month 1-3</div>
          <div class="flex-grow border-l-2 border-primary-200 pl-4 pb-4">
            <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">COE Processing</h4>
            <p class="text-neutral-600 text-sm">Employer submits COE application to regional Immigration Bureau. Processing typically takes 1-3 months. Larger companies with history have faster processing.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="flex gap-4">
          <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-24 text-sm font-medium text-primary-600">Month 3-4</div>
          <div class="flex-grow border-l-2 border-primary-200 pl-4 pb-4">
            <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Visa Application at Embassy</h4>
            <p class="text-neutral-600 text-sm">Receive COE by mail. Apply for visa at Japanese embassy/consulate in your country with COE. Visa typically issued within 1 week.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="flex gap-4">
          <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-24 text-sm font-medium text-primary-600">Week 1</div>
          <div class="flex-grow border-l-2 border-primary-200 pl-4 pb-4">
            <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Arrival & Residence Card</h4>
            <p class="text-neutral-600 text-sm">Arrive at designated airport. Receive Residence Card (Zairyu Card) at immigration. Valid for your visa duration. Can start working immediately.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="flex gap-4">
          <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-24 text-sm font-medium text-primary-600">Week 1-2</div>
          <div class="flex-grow border-l-2 border-primary-200 pl-4 pb-4">
            <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">City Registration & Bank</h4>
            <p class="text-neutral-600 text-sm">Register at city/ward office within 14 days. Open bank account (Zairyu card needed). Apply for My Number card (1-2 months to receive).</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="flex gap-4">
          <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-24 text-sm font-medium text-primary-600">Day 1 at Work</div>
          <div class="flex-grow border-l-2 border-primary-200 pl-4">
            <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Shakai Hoken Enrollment</h4>
            <p class="text-neutral-600 text-sm">Employer enrolls you in Shakai Hoken. Receive insurance card within 2-4 weeks. Coverage active from start date. Can use notification letter for care meanwhile.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Real-World Scenarios -->
    <section id="scenarios" class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Real-World Scenarios</h2>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-4">
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Software Engineer from USA</h4>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 text-sm mb-2">Mike, 28, joins Tokyo tech company. CS degree matches job. COE took 6 weeks. ¥7M salary qualifies for HSP with 75 points. 3-year path to PR. Shakai Hoken costs ¥100,000/month total but healthcare is almost free.</p>
          <p class="text-green-700 text-sm font-medium">Outcome: Smooth process, HSP benefits, affordable healthcare</p>
        </div>

        <div class="border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-4">
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">English Teacher (ALT)</h4>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 text-sm mb-2">Sarah, 24, joins JET Programme. Instructor visa (not Engineer). ¥3.6M salary. Full Shakai Hoken through employer. Healthcare visits cost ¥1,000-2,000. Added Aflac cancer insurance for peace of mind.</p>
          <p class="text-green-700 text-sm font-medium">Outcome: Different visa category but same excellent healthcare</p>
        </div>

        <div class="border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-4">
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Business Degree for Marketing Role</h4>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 text-sm mb-2">James, 30, has MBA from UK. Marketing manager role in Osaka. Degree clearly matches job. ¥8M salary. HSP with 78 points (bonus for top business school). Wife can work full-time on dependent visa.</p>
          <p class="text-green-700 text-sm font-medium">Outcome: MBA recognized, spouse work rights with HSP</p>
        </div>

        <div class="border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-4">
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Unrelated Degree Problem</h4>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 text-sm mb-2">Anna, 27, psychology degree but applying for IT role. Self-taught programmer. COE rejected—degree doesn't match position. Had to get 10 years experience verified or take psychology-related job instead.</p>
          <p class="text-red-700 text-sm font-medium">Outcome: Degree-job mismatch caused rejection</p>
        </div>

        <div class="border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-4">
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Family with Medical Needs</h4>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 text-sm mb-2">The Park family moves from Korea. Daughter has asthma requiring regular care. Shakai Hoken covers all treatment at 30% copay—about ¥3,000/month for inhalers and checkups. Kogaku cap means even hospitalizations are affordable.</p>
          <p class="text-green-700 text-sm font-medium">Outcome: Chronic conditions well-covered, costs predictable</p>
        </div>

        <div class="border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-4">
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Small Company COE Delay</h4>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 text-sm mb-2">Tom, 32, joins 5-person startup. First time company sponsored visa. COE processing took 3 months (longer scrutiny for new sponsors). Eventually approved but delayed start significantly. Should have negotiated remote start.</p>
          <p class="text-amber-700 text-sm font-medium">Outcome: Smaller companies mean longer processing times</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Common Mistakes -->
    <section id="common-mistakes" class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Common Mistakes to Avoid</h2>

      <div class="space-y-4">
        <div class="bg-red-50 border-l-4 border-red-400 p-4">
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-red-900">1. Degree Doesn't Match Job Duties</h4>
          <p class="text-red-800 text-sm">Immigration requires your university degree to relate to your job. A music degree for a programming job will be rejected. 10+ years of relevant work experience can substitute for degree mismatch, but must be documented thoroughly.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-red-50 border-l-4 border-red-400 p-4">
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-red-900">2. Not Registering at City Office Within 14 Days</h4>
          <p class="text-red-800 text-sm">You must register your address at the local ward/city office within 14 days of finding housing. This is required for bank accounts, My Number, and various services. Late registration can cause problems.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-red-50 border-l-4 border-red-400 p-4">
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-red-900">3. Assuming You Can Change Jobs Freely</h4>
          <p class="text-red-800 text-sm">Your visa is tied to status of residence category, not specific employer. You can change jobs within the same category (e.g., engineer to engineer) by notifying immigration within 14 days. Changing to a different category requires new visa application.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-red-50 border-l-4 border-red-400 p-4">
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-red-900">4. Not Carrying Insurance Card</h4>
          <p class="text-red-800 text-sm">Always carry your Shakai Hoken insurance card. Without it, you may pay 100% upfront at clinics (reimbursed later, but inconvenient). If card hasn't arrived yet, carry the enrollment notification from your employer.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-red-50 border-l-4 border-red-400 p-4">
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-red-900">5. Ignoring Pension Refund Option</h4>
          <p class="text-red-800 text-sm">If you leave Japan permanently, you can claim a lump-sum pension refund for contributions made (up to 5 years). Many expats forget this. Apply within 2 years of leaving Japan. Potentially hundreds of thousands of yen.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Healthcare Access -->
    <section id="healthcare-access" class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Healthcare System Access</h2>

      <p class="text-neutral-700 mb-4">
        Japan's healthcare system is excellent, with high-quality care at affordable prices. You can visit any clinic or hospital—there's no GP gatekeeper system. Walk-in clinics are common, and wait times are generally reasonable. The challenge is finding English-speaking providers outside major cities.
      </p>

